---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Publications | Vincenzo Di Perna"
  description="Selected publications, artifacts, and research outputs by Vincenzo Di Perna."
  sideBarActiveItemID="publications"
>
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Publications</h1>

    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed opacity-90">
      Selected publications, research artifacts, datasets, and working papers on
      blockchain systems, distributed infrastructures, benchmarking, reproducible
      experimentation, energy analysis, and digital assets.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-5">Selected peer-reviewed publications</h2>

    <div class="grid gap-5">
      <article class="card bg-base-100 shadow-sm">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 items-center">
            <h3 class="card-title">
              Topology-aware blockchain benchmarking
            </h3>
            <span class="badge badge-secondary">ACM DEBS'25</span>
          </div>

          <p>
            Research on how network topology, workload design, and controlled
            experimental conditions affect blockchain performance, energy usage,
            and variability.
          </p>

          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-2">
            <span class="badge badge-outline">Blockchain benchmarking</span>
            <span class="badge badge-outline">Network topology</span>
            <span class="badge badge-outline">Reproducibility</span>
            <span class="badge badge-outline">Energy analysis</span>
          </div>

          <div class="card-actions justify-end mt-4">
            <a
              class="btn btn-sm btn-outline"
              href="https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/3701717.3730540"
              target="_blank"
            >
              DOI / Paper
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="card bg-base-100 shadow-sm">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 items-center">
            <h3 class="card-title">
              Blockchain performance, energy, and economic efficiency
            </h3>
            <span class="badge badge-secondary">IEEE ICBC'25</span>
          </div>

          <p>
            Work connecting performance, energy consumption, and economic-efficiency
            dimensions in blockchain evaluation through reproducible experiments
            and data-driven analysis.
          </p>

          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-2">
            <span class="badge badge-outline">Performance</span>
            <span class="badge badge-outline">Energy</span>
            <span class="badge badge-outline">Economic efficiency</span>
            <span class="badge badge-outline">Digital assets</span>
          </div>

          <div class="card-actions justify-end mt-4">
            <a
              class="btn btn-sm btn-outline"
              href="https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/11114569"
              target="_blank"
            >
              IEEE Xplore
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="card bg-base-100 shadow-sm">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 items-center">
            <h3 class="card-title">
              Additional blockchain systems research
            </h3>
            <span class="badge badge-outline">Workshop / preprint</span>
          </div>

          <p>
            Additional research outputs on blockchain evaluation, decentralized
            infrastructures, protocol analysis, and related digital-asset topics.
          </p>

          <div class="card-actions justify-end mt-4">
            <a
              class="btn btn-sm btn-outline"
              href="https://ceur-ws.org/Vol-4105/paper09.pdf"
              target="_blank"
            >
              CEUR paper
            </a>

            <a
              class="btn btn-sm btn-outline"
              href="https://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=5034378"
              target="_blank"
            >
              SSRN
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-5">Research artifacts & datasets</h2>

    <div class="grid gap-5">
      <article class="card bg-base-100 shadow-sm">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 items-center">
            <h3 class="card-title">
              Lilith — A Topology-Aware Blockchain Benchmarking Framework
            </h3>
            <span class="badge badge-secondary">Artifact</span>
          </div>

          <p>
            Public research artifact supporting topology-aware blockchain
            benchmarking, workload execution, network emulation, and reproducible
            experimental analysis.
          </p>

          <div class="card-actions justify-end mt-4">
            <a
              class="btn btn-sm btn-outline"
              href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.11409100"
              target="_blank"
            >
              Zenodo DOI
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="card bg-base-100 shadow-sm">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 items-center">
            <h3 class="card-title">
              Blockchain Repeatability Dataset for Topology-Aware Benchmarking
            </h3>
            <span class="badge badge-secondary">Dataset</span>
          </div>

          <p>
            Dataset designed to quantify repeatability, variability, and performance
            predictability across blockchain platforms, workloads, and network
            topologies.
          </p>

          <div class="card-actions justify-end mt-4">
            <a
              class="btn btn-sm btn-outline"
              href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.15545963"
              target="_blank"
            >
              Zenodo DOI
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-5">Research themes</h2>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-sm">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h3 class="card-title">Blockchain systems evaluation</h3>
          <p>
            Performance, latency, throughput, topology effects, workload sensitivity,
            benchmarking methodology, and experimental reliability.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-sm">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h3 class="card-title">Energy and efficiency</h3>
          <p>
            Energy-aware blockchain analysis, normalized efficiency indicators,
            and trade-offs between performance, consumption, and protocol behavior.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-sm">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h3 class="card-title">Repeatability and predictability</h3>
          <p>
            Experimental repeatability, performance predictability, robust dispersion
            metrics, and statistical analysis of blockchain variability.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-sm">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h3 class="card-title">Digital assets and infrastructures</h3>
          <p>
            Digital-asset analytics, DeFi/CBDC-related systems, protocol data,
            and economic perspectives on decentralized infrastructures.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
